<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="AudioDevFilePerms" version="5.0">
 <title xml:id="fileDACs">Secure Audio Devices</title>
 <para>
  Restricts access to the audio device (
  <filename>/dev/audio*</filename> ) files.
  <indexterm>
   <primary>/dev</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <indexterm>
   <primary>Files and Directories</primary>
   <secondary>/dev</secondary>
  </indexterm>
 </para>
 <para>
  It is recommended to apply this module. The file permissions set by
  this module are operating system defaults; therefore, it should not
  impact normal operations.
 </para>
 <simplesect xml:id="AudioDevFilePerms-compliancy">
  <title>Compliancy</title>
  <itemizedlist>
   <title>CAG 20 Critical Security Controls (v2.3)</title>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     CC-3 - Secure Configurations for Hardware and Software on Laptops,
     Workstations, and Servers
    </para>
   </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <itemizedlist>
   <title>DISA Red Hat 5 STIG (V1R17)</title>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     GEN002320 - Audio devices must have mode 0660 or less permissive.
    </para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     GEN002340 - Audio devices must be owned by root.
    </para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     GEN002360 - Audio devices must be group-owned by root, sys, bin, or
     system.
    </para>
   </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <itemizedlist>
   <title>DISA UNIX STIG (v5 R1.30)</title>
